Of the 100 seats in the United States Senate, 54 are currently held by Republicans and 44 by Democrats. (Two are held by independents, who caucus with the Democrats). Thirty-four of these 100 seats are up for election in 2016, 24 of them currently held by a Republican.

Republicans must win at least 21 seats to guarantee a majority. Democrats must only win 15. Races below are grouped by Upshot forecast probability.